cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with generating natural language descriptions from photo streams, which is a problem in computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel neural network architecture, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves mining local storylines, which could be considered as an information retrieval task, falling under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
